    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup dry green or brown lentils, rinsed and drained</li>
            <li>1 onion, diced</li>
            <li>2 carrots, diced</li>
            <li>2 celery stalks, diced</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes</li>
            <li>6 cups vegetable broth</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground coriander</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon dried thyme</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>2 cups kale or spinach, chopped</li>
            <li>Juice of 1 lemon</li>
            <li>Fresh parsley for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a large pot, combine lentils, diced onion, carrots, celery, minced garlic, diced tomatoes, vegetable broth, ground cumin, ground coriander, smoked paprika, dried thyme, salt, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Bring the soup to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 25-30 minutes or until lentils and vegetables are tender.</li>
            <li>Add chopped kale or spinach to the soup and stir until wilted.</li>
            <li>Stir in the lemon juice and adjust seasoning with salt and black pepper to taste.</li>
            <li>Remove from heat and let the soup rest for a few minutes before serving.</li>
            <li>Garnish the Vegan Lentil Soup with fresh parsley.</li>
            <li>Serve hot and enjoy your comforting Vegan Lentil Soup!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

